1
00:00:55,980 --> 00:00:57,000
Whoever gets to the temple first, wins!

2
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,480
Let's get him!

3
00:01:02,481 --> 00:01:03,481
Hurry up!

4
00:01:04,960 --> 00:01:06,460
Hi, Nima.

5
00:01:12,961 --> 00:01:13,940
Good morning, Aang.

6
00:01:13,941 --> 00:01:14,540
Hey, my mirror.

7
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:15,340
Oh, hello, Aang.

8
00:01:15,420 --> 00:01:17,187
Oh, perfect timing.

9
00:01:23,421 --> 00:01:26,060
I don't mind giving me a lift.

10
00:01:26,140 --> 00:01:28,040
Piazzo, this isn't the best time.

11
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:29,700
I'm getting old, you know.

12
00:01:29,701 --> 00:01:32,280
My body doesn't move like it used to.

13
00:01:32,281 --> 00:01:34,180
I'm kind of in the middle of something.

14
00:01:34,181 --> 00:01:35,780
You are so heavy.

15
00:01:35,781 --> 00:01:36,380
Heavy?

16
00:01:36,381 --> 00:01:37,080
Me?

17
00:01:37,081 --> 00:01:38,960
I eat nothing but vegetables.

18
00:01:39,259 --> 00:01:40,580
Pie is not a vegetable.

19
00:01:40,581 --> 00:01:42,680
I'm gonna lose the race.

20
00:01:42,681 --> 00:01:43,300
Race?

21
00:01:43,301 --> 00:01:44,360
What race?

22
00:01:45,139 --> 00:01:46,120
We finally are!

23
00:01:46,121 --> 00:01:49,059
We won!

24
00:01:51,044 --> 00:01:56,044
Aang, as an airbender, it's important
that you know when to show restraint.

25
00:02:00,219 --> 00:02:04,120
Even if you have the power
to win, you are the Avatar.

26
00:02:04,980 --> 00:02:08,699
A lot of people are
going to rely on the Isle.

27
00:02:13,380 --> 00:02:14,880
He's gone!

28
00:02:21,381 --> 00:02:22,380
He ran away!

29
00:02:22,381 --> 00:02:22,680
What?

30
00:02:22,681 --> 00:02:23,580
I'm here!

31
00:02:23,581 --> 00:02:25,400
Where's the Avatar?

32
00:02:25,401 --> 00:02:26,840
I'm here!

33
00:02:26,841 --> 00:02:29,580
Aang, where are you?

34
00:02:29,581 --> 00:02:31,100
Piazzo, I'm here!

35
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:36,160
I'm here!

36
00:02:43,890 --> 00:02:45,390
Hey, Momo.

37
00:02:47,241 --> 00:02:49,540
Hi, Appa.

38
00:02:49,541 --> 00:02:51,140
Was I asleep for long?

39
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,640
Okay, okay.

40
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:53,960
I'm awake already.

41
00:02:54,410 --> 00:02:55,160
I know, I know.

42
00:02:55,410 --> 00:02:56,340
We've got a job to finish.

43
00:02:56,341 --> 00:02:59,440
Let's continue our journey.

44
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:01,540
Back to our old home.

45
00:03:46,980 --> 00:03:50,403
This may not have been
our best trip, but any

46
00:03:50,415 --> 00:03:54,080
airbender relic we find
makes it all worthwhile.

47
00:03:56,130 --> 00:03:59,897
This could be the oldest
piece in our collection.

48
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:06,480
So numb.

49
00:04:21,650 --> 00:04:23,300
I miss you.

50
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,660
Momo, go outside with Appa.

51
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,440
Now!

52
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:38,400
Who are you?

53
00:04:44,901 --> 00:04:46,320
Why are you doing this?

54
00:04:46,321 --> 00:04:47,821
Please, stop!

55
00:04:51,321 --> 00:04:52,860
I don't want to hurt you.

56
00:04:52,861 --> 00:04:54,361
Where is it?

57
00:04:57,621 --> 00:04:58,320
Where is it?

58
00:04:58,321 --> 00:04:59,640
Nope, that's not it.

59
00:04:59,641 --> 00:05:00,140
Hey!

60
00:05:00,141 --> 00:05:01,141
Those are antiques!

61
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:07,290
Enough!

62
00:05:13,641 --> 00:05:15,141
Wait!

63
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:19,020
I found it!

64
00:05:19,021 --> 00:05:21,321
Zonam, why ain't after you?

65
00:05:35,060 --> 00:05:36,560
Wait!

66
00:05:43,061 --> 00:05:45,694
No, that's a thousand years old!

67
00:05:48,681 --> 00:05:49,920
Give it to me!

68
00:05:49,921 --> 00:05:51,140
Why don't we just talk?

69
00:05:51,141 --> 00:05:52,140
Maybe I can help.

70
00:05:52,141 --> 00:05:53,140
We don't need your help, Avatar.

71
00:05:53,141 --> 00:05:55,140
We're done living in a world where Vendors
have all the power and we have none!

72
00:05:55,141 --> 00:05:56,140
Who are you?

73
00:05:56,141 --> 00:05:57,140
We're the Denied!

74
00:05:57,141 --> 00:05:58,140
The Denied?

75
00:05:58,141 --> 00:05:59,140
Just kill him already!

76
00:05:59,141 --> 00:06:00,140
No!

77
00:06:00,141 --> 00:06:01,140
He'll bring the whole place down!

78
00:06:01,141 --> 00:06:03,140
have all the power and we have none.

79
00:06:03,141 --> 00:06:04,140
Who are you?

80
00:06:04,141 --> 00:06:05,140
We're the Denied!

81
00:06:05,141 --> 00:06:06,140
The Denied?

82
00:06:06,141 --> 00:06:08,140
Just kill him already!

83
00:06:08,141 --> 00:06:10,140
No! He'll bring the whole place down!

84
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:33,707
You... saved me.

85
00:06:40,141 --> 00:06:43,140
Kaliq! Grab the map! Let's go!

86
00:06:50,140 --> 00:06:51,640
Oh no!

87
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:03,140
Oh no!

88
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:33,140
I'm fine. Momo, I'm fine.

89
00:07:33,141 --> 00:07:35,140
I'm fine. Momo, I'm fine.

90
00:07:35,141 --> 00:07:37,140
We've got to get to Republic City.

91
00:07:37,141 --> 00:07:39,140
Appa, yip yip!

92
00:07:39,141 --> 00:07:41,140
I'm fine. Momo, I'm fine.

93
00:07:41,141 --> 00:07:43,140
We've got to get to Republic City.

94
00:07:43,141 --> 00:07:45,140
Appa, yip yip!

95
00:07:45,141 --> 00:07:47,140
I'm fine. Momo, I'm fine.

96
00:07:47,141 --> 00:07:49,140
We've got to get to Republic City.

97
00:07:49,141 --> 00:07:51,140
Appa, yip yip!

98
00:07:51,141 --> 00:07:54,140
I'm fine. Momo, I'm fine.

99
00:07:54,141 --> 00:07:56,140
I'm fine. Momo, I'm fine.

100
00:07:56,141 --> 00:07:58,140
We've got to get to Republic City.

101
00:07:58,590 --> 00:08:00,140
Appa, yip yip!

102
00:08:00,141 --> 00:08:04,140
We've got to get to Republic City.

103
00:08:04,141 --> 00:08:05,140
Appa, yip yip!

104
00:08:05,141 --> 00:08:06,141
Yip yip!

105
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:17,640
Water.

106
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:27,140
Her tribes gather strength from the moon.

107
00:08:27,141 --> 00:08:29,241
And flow with the tides.

108
00:08:32,140 --> 00:08:33,140
Earth.

109
00:08:33,141 --> 00:08:36,140
A kingdom of unshakable will.

110
00:08:36,141 --> 00:08:38,140
Reliable and strong.

111
00:08:38,141 --> 00:08:39,641
Fire.

112
00:08:43,141 --> 00:08:46,140
A nation capable of great destruction.

113
00:08:46,141 --> 00:08:48,508
But also... of great warmth.

114
00:08:51,141 --> 00:08:54,140
Air.

115
00:08:54,141 --> 00:08:57,140
Peaceful nomads with
the power of a hurricane.

116
00:08:57,141 --> 00:09:00,140
But the spirit of a gentle breeze.

117
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:07,084
For generations, the
Avatar, the one master of

118
00:09:07,096 --> 00:09:11,140
all four elements, kept
the nations in balance.

119
00:09:11,141 --> 00:09:17,140
But when that responsibility
fell to me as a child, I ran away.

120
00:09:17,514 --> 00:09:20,140
I was caught in a deadly storm.

121
00:09:20,141 --> 00:09:23,128
But my Avatar spirit
preserved me in a sphere

122
00:09:23,140 --> 00:09:26,140
of energy where I stayed
for a hundred years.

123
00:09:27,140 --> 00:09:30,304
I woke to discover that
the balance preserved

124
00:09:30,316 --> 00:09:33,140
by the Avatar had
been destroyed by war.

125
00:09:33,141 --> 00:09:36,140
The air nomads were gone.

126
00:09:36,141 --> 00:09:38,140
All but one.

127
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:40,140
me.

128
00:09:40,141 --> 00:09:44,140
I could no longer run from
my responsibility as the Avatar.

129
00:09:44,141 --> 00:09:47,140
I found allies from every nation.

130
00:09:47,141 --> 00:09:49,140
Benders.

131
00:09:49,141 --> 00:09:51,140
And non-benders.

132
00:09:51,141 --> 00:09:54,140
Katara taught me how to water bend.

133
00:09:54,141 --> 00:09:57,140
Toph trained me in the
ways of the Earthbenders.

134
00:09:58,140 --> 00:10:03,140
Zuko, once my worst enemy,
became my firebending teacher.

135
00:10:03,141 --> 00:10:08,140
Sokka showed me that bravery is the
most important part of being a leader.

136
00:10:08,141 --> 00:10:11,140
We became a family.

137
00:10:11,141 --> 00:10:14,574
And together, we ended
the Hundred Year War.

138
00:10:17,839 --> 00:10:22,140
Then, we began the hard
work of rebuilding the world.

139
00:10:29,140 --> 00:10:32,507
For so long, the nation stood apart, alone.

140
00:10:37,141 --> 00:10:39,140
And we all suffered as a result.

141
00:10:40,389 --> 00:10:45,140
But here, on this ancient site, we created
a place where all people are welcome.

142
00:10:45,141 --> 00:10:48,140
Bender and non-bender alike.

143
00:10:48,689 --> 00:10:51,140
Working together in
peace to build the future.

144
00:10:51,339 --> 00:10:57,140
Though there are still those who
would seek to divide us, we remain united.

145
00:10:59,140 --> 00:11:03,335
As a council representative, I am
honored to be here today, celebrating

146
00:11:03,347 --> 00:11:07,140
the anniversary of Republic City
and the opening of Unity Tower.

147
00:11:07,539 --> 00:11:09,140
A symbol for all people.

148
00:11:09,141 --> 00:11:10,641
Look!

149
00:11:17,141 --> 00:11:20,140
It's the Avatar!

150
00:11:20,141 --> 00:11:21,641
Let's hurry!

151
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:29,140
Oh.

152
00:11:29,589 --> 00:11:31,089
Momo!

153
00:11:33,339 --> 00:11:34,839
Appa!

154
00:11:37,141 --> 00:11:39,140
I missed you too, old friend.

155
00:11:41,339 --> 00:11:42,140
Aang!

156
00:11:42,141 --> 00:11:43,140
Katara!

157
00:11:43,141 --> 00:11:44,641
You're hurt.

158
00:11:58,239 --> 00:11:59,140
Take a deep breath.

159
00:11:59,141 --> 00:12:00,641
And... Exhale.

160
00:12:05,139 --> 00:12:07,140
I've heard the Deneid
are growing in numbers,

161
00:12:07,389 --> 00:12:09,140
but they've never done anything like this.

162
00:12:09,141 --> 00:12:10,140
Attacking the Avatar?

163
00:12:10,141 --> 00:12:11,140
Yeah.

164
00:12:11,141 --> 00:12:14,140
They were incredible fighters.

165
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:16,140
Even without bending.

166
00:12:16,489 --> 00:12:18,140
Oops!

167
00:12:18,141 --> 00:12:19,140
Ow!

168
00:12:19,141 --> 00:12:20,140
Breathe through it.

169
00:12:20,141 --> 00:12:21,140
Be honest.

170
00:12:21,141 --> 00:12:22,140
You're enjoying this.

171
00:12:22,141 --> 00:12:24,140
Aang, this is serious.

172
00:12:24,789 --> 00:12:29,140
Whatever this map they took was, if they
were willing to kill the Avatar to get it,

173
00:12:29,539 --> 00:12:31,140
what else are they willing to do?

174
00:12:31,141 --> 00:12:32,140
I don't know.

175
00:12:32,141 --> 00:12:35,140
I'm worried about you.

176
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:38,140
You're spending more and
more time at the Air Temple.

177
00:12:38,141 --> 00:12:39,141
Alone.

178
00:12:39,239 --> 00:12:41,939
It's... how I hold
on to my past.

179
00:12:45,839 --> 00:12:48,140
I know how hard this is for you.

180
00:12:52,289 --> 00:12:54,140
When I was attacked,

181
00:12:54,739 --> 00:12:58,140
all I could think about
was that... this could be it.

182
00:13:00,539 --> 00:13:02,140
I'm the last Airbender.

183
00:13:02,140 --> 00:13:05,140
If I die,

184
00:13:06,689 --> 00:13:08,140
my culture dies with me.

185
00:13:11,140 --> 00:13:12,165
You may be the last Airbender.

186
00:13:12,189 --> 00:13:13,140
You may be the last Airbender.

187
00:13:13,141 --> 00:13:14,140
But you're not alone.

188
00:13:14,141 --> 00:13:15,140
You're not alone.

189
00:13:15,141 --> 00:13:17,140
Aang,

190
00:13:17,439 --> 00:13:19,140
none of this would exist without you.

191
00:13:21,039 --> 00:13:24,140
You made the city possible
with your heart and your mind.

192
00:13:24,141 --> 00:13:27,140
Because of you,

193
00:13:28,114 --> 00:13:29,140
all of the nations live here.

194
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:30,140
Together.

195
00:13:30,141 --> 00:13:31,140
Together.

196
00:13:31,141 --> 00:13:34,140
All except mine.

197
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:39,640
I know.

198
00:13:47,789 --> 00:13:49,669
But the people here
still need your protection.

199
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:51,140
You're an Airbender.

200
00:13:52,889 --> 00:13:54,140
But you're also the Avatar.

201
00:13:54,141 --> 00:13:57,140
You're right.

202
00:13:59,589 --> 00:14:02,141
Whoever this Sonam person
is, I need to find out more.

203
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:21,140
Aang.

204
00:14:21,141 --> 00:14:22,140
Avatar Roku.

205
00:14:22,141 --> 00:14:23,140
It is good to see you again.

206
00:14:23,141 --> 00:14:24,140
How can I help you?

207
00:14:24,141 --> 00:14:27,140
In your lifetime, did you ever hear of
an ancient Airbender named Sonam?

208
00:14:27,141 --> 00:14:29,140
I have not.

209
00:14:29,141 --> 00:14:30,415
But you have many past lives to call upon.

210
00:14:30,439 --> 00:14:34,140
Perhaps one further back in
the Avatar Cycle can help you.

211
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:36,140
Thank you, Avatar.

212
00:14:36,141 --> 00:14:37,140
Roku.

213
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:37,140
I'm sorry.

214
00:14:37,141 --> 00:14:38,140
I've never heard her say.

215
00:14:38,141 --> 00:14:39,140
Perhaps earlier.

216
00:14:39,140 --> 00:14:41,140
Not here.

217
00:14:41,141 --> 00:14:43,708
We're back in the Avatar Cycle.

218
00:14:48,141 --> 00:14:53,141
We're back in the back of the Cycle.

219
00:15:08,989 --> 00:15:11,140
Um, hello?

220
00:15:12,089 --> 00:15:13,140
Is there anyone here?

221
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:15,539
Hello?

222
00:15:18,140 --> 00:15:22,240
Who calls upon Avatar Sion's
vast wealth of knowledge?

223
00:15:26,814 --> 00:15:28,140
Oh, hello.

224
00:15:28,639 --> 00:15:31,140
You look like an Avatar from
a time quite distant from mine.

225
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:34,140
Please, please, tell me about your era.

226
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:36,140
What are people wearing?

227
00:15:36,289 --> 00:15:37,140
Are sandals still a thing?

228
00:15:37,141 --> 00:15:39,140
Uh, yes.

229
00:15:39,239 --> 00:15:40,140
Oh, why?

230
00:15:40,239 --> 00:15:45,239
Why, after so many years, open toes,
seeing someone else's crusty cuticles?

231
00:15:47,141 --> 00:15:48,140
Disgusting!

232
00:15:48,141 --> 00:15:49,141
Right.

233
00:15:49,189 --> 00:15:52,140
Anyway, I have come through your guidance.

234
00:15:52,141 --> 00:15:53,141
You see, I was attacked.

235
00:15:53,239 --> 00:15:55,140
It was not me, okay?

236
00:15:55,141 --> 00:15:56,141
It wasn't me.

237
00:15:56,189 --> 00:15:57,189
I know that.

238
00:15:57,614 --> 00:16:00,140
I think it might have something to
do with an airbender named Sonam.

239
00:16:00,141 --> 00:16:01,141
Hmm.

240
00:16:01,289 --> 00:16:02,140
Sonam.

241
00:16:02,141 --> 00:16:04,140
It sounds familiar.

242
00:16:04,141 --> 00:16:05,141
Sonam.

243
00:16:05,439 --> 00:16:07,140
Where have I heard that name before?

244
00:16:07,141 --> 00:16:08,140
Aha!

245
00:16:08,141 --> 00:16:10,066
Sonam was the youngest
daughter of the owner of

246
00:16:10,078 --> 00:16:12,140
the possum chicken shop
at the corner marketplace.

247
00:16:12,141 --> 00:16:13,141
Wait.

248
00:16:13,189 --> 00:16:15,140
That was my ex, Soniam.

249
00:16:15,439 --> 00:16:18,140
If only she didn't have
those humongous toenails.

250
00:16:18,339 --> 00:16:20,140
Ugh, disgusting.

251
00:16:20,141 --> 00:16:21,141
This is going nowhere.

252
00:16:21,189 --> 00:16:22,689
Sonam?

253
00:16:26,141 --> 00:16:27,140
Well, thank you for your time.

254
00:16:27,141 --> 00:16:28,140
I must continue my search.

255
00:16:28,141 --> 00:16:29,140
Oh!

256
00:16:29,141 --> 00:16:30,140
Sonam!

257
00:16:30,141 --> 00:16:33,140
You're asking about the
legend of the lost Avatar.

258
00:16:33,141 --> 00:16:36,140
Sonam was an Avatar?

259
00:16:36,141 --> 00:16:37,140
Indeed she was!

260
00:16:37,141 --> 00:16:42,140
She was the Avatar in the
golden age of airbenders.

261
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:47,296
Legend said she had a staff
that could channel the vast energy

262
00:16:47,308 --> 00:16:51,140
of the spirit world, granting
its keeper unlimited power.

263
00:16:51,141 --> 00:16:54,140
Is-is that even possible?

264
00:16:54,141 --> 00:16:57,140
Eh, we'll never know for sure.

265
00:16:57,164 --> 00:17:00,140
Many Avatars have tried to
communicate with her, but they couldn't.

266
00:17:00,789 --> 00:17:05,140
She disappeared so completely
that it was as if she never existed.

267
00:17:06,189 --> 00:17:08,140
And perhaps it's better that way.

268
00:17:08,339 --> 00:17:12,140
Maybe such a staff was too
dangerous for anyone to possess.

269
00:17:12,889 --> 00:17:14,140
Even the Avatar.

270
00:17:14,141 --> 00:17:17,140
But-but that's exactly
why I need to find it.

271
00:17:17,539 --> 00:17:19,215
The people who attacked
me discovered a map.

272
00:17:19,239 --> 00:17:22,140
It must lead to the staff.

273
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:23,140
Avatar Shion.

274
00:17:23,141 --> 00:17:24,141
Please.

275
00:17:24,389 --> 00:17:26,140
You have to tell me where it is.

276
00:17:28,889 --> 00:17:34,140
The legend says that Sonam disappeared
with her staff on the peak of Mount Baihu.

277
00:17:34,141 --> 00:17:35,641
Katara.

278
00:17:38,389 --> 00:17:40,140
I'm sorry to leave so suddenly.

279
00:17:40,314 --> 00:17:42,140
But I found out what the denier after.

280
00:17:43,339 --> 00:17:45,140
Sonam had a staff of immense power.

281
00:17:45,141 --> 00:17:48,140
And in their hands, it could
be a devastating weapon.

282
00:17:48,141 --> 00:17:50,140
They have a head start.

283
00:17:50,239 --> 00:17:52,140
There's no time to waste.

284
00:17:52,141 --> 00:17:55,140
You take Appa and Momo and
gather up the rest of the team.

285
00:17:55,141 --> 00:17:57,140
We're gonna need some help.

286
00:18:04,140 --> 00:18:08,390
Next on the agenda, a Fire Nation
naval vessel came into conflict

287
00:18:08,402 --> 00:18:12,140
with an extremist group of
non-benders called the Denied.

288
00:18:12,141 --> 00:18:14,140
They've been robbing
ancient sites- Your Majesty!

289
00:18:14,140 --> 00:18:14,140
Your Majesty!

290
00:18:14,141 --> 00:18:15,141
Your Majesty!

291
00:18:15,489 --> 00:18:17,140
An urgent message has
arrived from Republic City!

292
00:18:17,141 --> 00:18:18,140
How impudent!

293
00:18:18,141 --> 00:18:21,141
Can't you see Fire Lord
Zuko's- Chamberlain.

294
00:18:23,289 --> 00:18:25,103
There's only one person
who can send a message

295
00:18:25,115 --> 00:18:27,140
urgent enough to interrupt
the Fire Lord's council.

296
00:18:27,141 --> 00:18:28,140
Is it from the Avatar?

297
00:18:28,141 --> 00:18:29,140
Yes, my lord.

298
00:18:29,141 --> 00:18:30,140
Read it to me.

299
00:18:30,141 --> 00:18:31,141
Yes, my lord.

300
00:18:32,639 --> 00:18:34,406
What are you doing?

301
00:18:37,141 --> 00:18:38,141
Read it quickly.

302
00:18:38,639 --> 00:18:40,140
Yes, Gwen Chamberlain.

303
00:18:40,189 --> 00:18:45,140
Flame Hill Hartman, how's
ruling the Fire Nation?

304
00:18:45,539 --> 00:18:51,140
I hope the boring Chamberlain you mentioned
in your letters isn't still annoying you.

305
00:18:51,141 --> 00:18:55,140
Anywho, to cut to the
chase, I need your help.

306
00:18:55,189 --> 00:18:57,140
Can you please come immediately?

307
00:18:57,264 --> 00:19:01,140
Oh, and don't forget to
bring some firecracker buns.

308
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,773
Allow me to present Sokka Cycle.

309
00:19:06,141 --> 00:19:10,140
Flames launch you into the sky where
you can drop water bombs on your enemies.

310
00:19:10,539 --> 00:19:13,140
Then skis pop out to
help you stick the landing.

311
00:19:13,239 --> 00:19:15,140
Pretty great, right?

312
00:19:15,141 --> 00:19:16,141
Eh, boring.

313
00:19:16,189 --> 00:19:18,316
Why would you need a sled
when you can just waterbend?

314
00:19:18,340 --> 00:19:19,140
Oh, oh, oh!

315
00:19:19,141 --> 00:19:20,140
Like me, like me!

316
00:19:20,141 --> 00:19:24,140
Keep in mind, there are still plenty
of folks like me who can't bend.

317
00:19:24,165 --> 00:19:27,140
Why would Avatar Aang
partner with a non-bender?

318
00:19:27,339 --> 00:19:29,140
Why? I'll tell you why.

319
00:19:29,141 --> 00:19:31,140
I saved him from the iceberg.

320
00:19:31,141 --> 00:19:35,140
My boomerang flew by his side while I
carried away enemies with my trusty blade.

321
00:19:35,141 --> 00:19:38,140
I even took down the whole
Fire Nation airship armada.

322
00:19:40,140 --> 00:19:43,140
And on top of all that, I
was more popular than him.

323
00:19:43,141 --> 00:19:46,140
You're such a liar, Sokka.

324
00:19:46,141 --> 00:19:48,041
It's from the Avatar.

325
00:19:50,141 --> 00:19:51,140
Wow!

326
00:19:51,141 --> 00:19:52,141
Really?

327
00:19:52,389 --> 00:19:54,140
Oh, so now you think I'm cool?

328
00:19:54,141 --> 00:19:57,140
All right, metalbenders.

329
00:19:57,141 --> 00:20:01,140
Let's see if any of you tenderfoots
can at least make me use my hands.

330
00:20:01,141 --> 00:20:03,140
my hands.

331
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:35,400
I'm still the greatest
Earthbender in the world!

332
00:20:39,949 --> 00:20:41,320
And I'm bored.

333
00:20:41,321 --> 00:20:43,820
Master Toph, there's a bird on your head.

334
00:20:43,821 --> 00:20:44,820
And?

335
00:20:44,821 --> 00:20:46,360
It looks like it has a message.

336
00:20:46,361 --> 00:20:47,361
Reed.

337
00:20:48,209 --> 00:20:49,540
Uh, it's from Avatar Aang.

338
00:20:49,541 --> 00:20:50,540
He needs your help.

339
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:53,639
It's the deni-- The
deni-- Where is he?

340
00:20:53,739 --> 00:20:54,739
Mount Bayou.

341
00:21:01,140 --> 00:21:02,140
Oh, my God.

342
00:21:31,140 --> 00:21:36,140
No.

343
00:21:47,141 --> 00:21:50,140
I love that hat.

344
00:22:06,140 --> 00:22:11,140
Oh, my God.

345
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:43,840
Sonam?

346
00:23:50,341 --> 00:23:52,041
Could that be you?

347
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:30,020
I'm not going to die.

348
00:24:55,019 --> 00:24:56,519
Who are you?

349
00:25:02,119 --> 00:25:07,119
Huh?

350
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:28,800
I don't know.

351
00:28:31,929 --> 00:28:33,435
Did you come off to get yourself killed?

352
00:28:33,459 --> 00:28:35,219
I thought you were
here looking for a staff.

353
00:28:35,939 --> 00:28:36,939
Who's this guy?

354
00:28:44,189 --> 00:28:45,189
An airbender.

355
00:29:06,429 --> 00:29:08,380
How did he hold up an entire mountain?

356
00:29:09,029 --> 00:29:11,880
His chi is strong, like
nothing I've ever felt.

357
00:29:13,579 --> 00:29:17,980
Hey, Avatar, you think this guy beat
your record for longest frozen airbender?

358
00:29:18,469 --> 00:29:21,080
Yeah, how long do you
think he was in that ice?

359
00:29:21,629 --> 00:29:22,629
I don't know.

360
00:29:23,239 --> 00:29:25,100
His tattoos look ancient.

361
00:29:26,099 --> 00:29:27,640
He's been in there a long time.

362
00:29:28,339 --> 00:29:29,440
He smells good for an old guy.

363
00:29:29,441 --> 00:29:29,900
Ew.

364
00:29:30,180 --> 00:29:30,720
What?

365
00:29:30,721 --> 00:29:32,460
My senses tell me this
guy is pretty attractive.

366
00:29:32,461 --> 00:29:32,860
Tom!

367
00:29:32,959 --> 00:29:33,780
Someone else confirm.

368
00:29:33,781 --> 00:29:34,540
This is serious.

369
00:29:34,541 --> 00:29:35,820
What does attractive even mean?

370
00:29:35,821 --> 00:29:37,160
Just give me a straight confirmation.

371
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,220
Is he attractive?

372
00:29:38,221 --> 00:29:39,340
He's very attractive.

373
00:29:39,341 --> 00:29:40,341
Huh?

374
00:29:41,360 --> 00:29:41,760
What?

375
00:29:41,761 --> 00:29:42,880
He is.

376
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:42,880
He is.

377
00:29:43,479 --> 00:29:44,400
It's all in the bone structure.

378
00:29:44,401 --> 00:29:45,240
No.

379
00:29:45,241 --> 00:29:46,241
No.

380
00:29:48,669 --> 00:29:51,060
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

381
00:29:51,061 --> 00:29:51,720
Hey.

382
00:29:51,820 --> 00:29:52,580
Easy.

383
00:29:52,581 --> 00:29:53,760
You're safe.

384
00:29:53,761 --> 00:29:55,261
Earthbender!

385
00:29:57,280 --> 00:29:58,880
No, no, no, we're all friends here.

386
00:29:58,930 --> 00:29:59,930
It's okay.

387
00:30:00,599 --> 00:30:02,480
Someone woke up on the
wrong side of the mountain.

388
00:30:02,481 --> 00:30:04,620
Where is she?

389
00:30:06,619 --> 00:30:07,820
Where is Avatar Sonam?

390
00:30:08,769 --> 00:30:09,560
You knew Sonam?

391
00:30:09,561 --> 00:30:11,900
Who are you?

392
00:30:13,649 --> 00:30:17,540
I don't know how to explain it, but
you've been asleep for a long time.

393
00:30:19,089 --> 00:30:20,180
I'm the Avatar now.

394
00:30:20,181 --> 00:30:21,440
I'm Aang.

395
00:30:23,339 --> 00:30:27,540
If you're the Avatar,
then... Sonam.

396
00:30:30,749 --> 00:30:33,658
Well, Sonam might be
long gone, but on the

397
00:30:33,670 --> 00:30:36,800
bright side, you woke
up at the perfect time.

398
00:30:37,149 --> 00:30:39,480
Everyone will be amazed
to see another airbender.

399
00:30:39,779 --> 00:30:41,460
Aang's not the last one anymore.

400
00:30:43,409 --> 00:30:45,140
What do you mean, last?

401
00:30:49,989 --> 00:30:50,989
The air nomads.

402
00:30:52,209 --> 00:30:53,209
They've been wiped out.

403
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:55,840
There's only me.

404
00:30:55,841 --> 00:30:58,600
No.

405
00:31:00,249 --> 00:31:00,900
Sonam's staff.

406
00:31:00,901 --> 00:31:02,500
Do you have it?

407
00:31:03,699 --> 00:31:04,540
It's our only hope now.

408
00:31:04,541 --> 00:31:06,260
What do you mean?

409
00:31:07,109 --> 00:31:08,149
I thought it was a weapon.

410
00:31:09,949 --> 00:31:10,960
The staff is no weapon.

411
00:31:12,309 --> 00:31:13,309
It is a gift.

412
00:31:13,889 --> 00:31:18,889
With it, Sonam was able to channel
the vast power of the spirit world.

413
00:31:21,619 --> 00:31:24,720
It was this power that
allowed Jurana to flourish.

414
00:31:25,060 --> 00:31:27,480
The greatest city in the world.

415
00:31:29,060 --> 00:31:32,905
An air nomad utopia where
Sonam presided over a golden

416
00:31:32,917 --> 00:31:37,060
age of balance and where I
devoted my life to serving her.

417
00:31:38,380 --> 00:31:42,521
In return, she raised me
up and used her staff to give

418
00:31:42,533 --> 00:31:46,380
me, a lowly non-bender,
the power to bend the air.

419
00:31:47,679 --> 00:31:50,140
I was the first, but I
would not be the last.

420
00:31:50,141 --> 00:31:54,079
She filled the skies with
airbenders, and we flew

421
00:31:54,091 --> 00:31:57,800
by her side, spreading
peace across the world.

422
00:32:07,039 --> 00:32:08,640
Aang, are you okay?

423
00:32:08,641 --> 00:32:13,000
Sonam used the staff to
give people airbending.

424
00:32:14,499 --> 00:32:19,720
If we found it, I could bring
airbending back to the world.

425
00:32:20,569 --> 00:32:21,880
This is incredible!

426
00:32:21,881 --> 00:32:24,400
There haven't been airbenders
for over a hundred years!

427
00:32:24,649 --> 00:32:27,760
This is everything you ever wanted, Aang.

428
00:32:29,859 --> 00:32:33,480
We could heal the greatest atrocity
my nation committed in the war.

429
00:32:34,829 --> 00:32:37,140
This could be the final
step to rebuilding the world.

430
00:32:37,989 --> 00:32:39,500
Not if the Denied get there first.

431
00:32:39,999 --> 00:32:40,999
They have the map.

432
00:32:42,319 --> 00:32:43,319
Who are the Denied?

433
00:32:43,649 --> 00:32:45,160
A group of violent non-benders.

434
00:32:46,009 --> 00:32:49,860
They... They must be after the
staff to give themselves airbending.

435
00:32:50,459 --> 00:32:51,659
Then there's no time to waste.

436
00:32:52,219 --> 00:32:53,619
There's only one place it could be.

437
00:32:54,209 --> 00:32:55,209
Ready your bison.

438
00:32:55,389 --> 00:32:57,800
We'll need to travel
across the endless ocean.

439
00:32:58,249 --> 00:32:59,489
On the other side of the world?

440
00:33:00,119 --> 00:33:01,319
But there's nothing out there.

441
00:33:01,459 --> 00:33:02,140
There's an island.

442
00:33:02,141 --> 00:33:04,400
The journey will not be easy.

443
00:33:04,974 --> 00:33:06,220
But we can make it.

444
00:33:07,494 --> 00:33:08,494
Then let's get going.

445
00:33:09,189 --> 00:33:12,280
The skies are no place for a water child.

446
00:33:13,140 --> 00:33:18,140
I know you just woke up after thousands
of years, but we do these things together.

447
00:33:20,101 --> 00:33:21,101
Trust me.

448
00:33:21,719 --> 00:33:22,719
We're stronger this way.

449
00:33:23,039 --> 00:33:24,240
Welcome to Team Avatar.

450
00:33:24,241 --> 00:33:25,900
What's your name?

451
00:33:25,901 --> 00:33:27,500
Taga.

452
00:33:27,501 --> 00:33:29,800
My name is Taga.

453
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:37,673
Just think of it as a big metal airbison.

454
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:49,060
We will travel ancient
paths through the sky.

455
00:33:54,069 --> 00:33:57,567
Ones that our people
learned by following the great

456
00:33:57,579 --> 00:34:01,020
airbison herds that long
ago taught us airbending.

457
00:34:01,021 --> 00:34:04,080
Air currents known only to us.

458
00:34:04,779 --> 00:34:07,340
Encircling the great sphere of existence.

459
00:34:07,341 --> 00:34:10,199
Allowing us to travel where we wish.

460
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:12,320
Giving us our name.

461
00:34:12,321 --> 00:34:14,780
The Air Nomads.

462
00:34:14,781 --> 00:34:19,781
Allowing us to travel where we wish.

463
00:34:31,740 --> 00:34:32,600
Allowing us to travel.

464
00:34:32,601 --> 00:34:35,600
Allowing us to travel where we wish.

465
00:34:35,601 --> 00:34:40,601
Allowing us to travel.

466
00:34:59,601 --> 00:35:00,600
We wish.

467
00:35:00,601 --> 00:35:01,600
Uh, no!

468
00:35:01,601 --> 00:35:02,600
No!

469
00:35:02,601 --> 00:35:04,600
He was frozen for 5,000 years.

470
00:35:04,700 --> 00:35:05,600
Okay?

471
00:35:05,601 --> 00:35:06,600
You were frozen for what?

472
00:35:06,601 --> 00:35:07,601
A hundred?

473
00:35:07,775 --> 00:35:08,600
Okay?

474
00:35:08,601 --> 00:35:09,600
That's nothing.

475
00:35:09,601 --> 00:35:11,601
Your brain is... fresh.

476
00:35:11,900 --> 00:35:13,600
Maybe he is a little old-fashioned.

477
00:35:13,601 --> 00:35:14,601
But look at him.

478
00:35:15,150 --> 00:35:16,600
He's so in tune with his element.

479
00:35:16,601 --> 00:35:19,600
He can travel across the entire ocean.

480
00:35:19,601 --> 00:35:20,600
With no map.

481
00:35:20,601 --> 00:35:21,600
No instruments.

482
00:35:21,601 --> 00:35:24,568
There's so much I can learn from him.

483
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:37,767
I'd give anything to be able
to see my air bison again.

484
00:35:41,601 --> 00:35:44,434
And now... To see
only one remains.

485
00:35:53,250 --> 00:35:54,650
You said our people were wiped out.

486
00:35:55,750 --> 00:35:56,600
Yet you survived.

487
00:35:56,601 --> 00:35:57,600
How?

488
00:35:57,601 --> 00:36:00,634
I had just found out I was the Avatar.

489
00:36:02,601 --> 00:36:05,601
But... The responsibility...

490
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:07,800
It was too much.

491
00:36:09,450 --> 00:36:10,600
So I ran away.

492
00:36:10,601 --> 00:36:14,600
While I was gone... The
Fire Nation attacked.

493
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:18,600
They were looking for me.

494
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:25,600
If... If I'd just been
there... Sonam would say...

495
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:28,600
Air Nomads are formed from the mist.

496
00:36:30,250 --> 00:36:31,810
We walk the world for a moment in time.

497
00:36:33,150 --> 00:36:35,600
Then we return to the eternal wind.

498
00:36:35,601 --> 00:36:38,600
Monkiazzo taught me that.

499
00:36:38,650 --> 00:36:41,600
We carry the same weight.

500
00:36:41,601 --> 00:36:44,600
A grief no one else could
possibly comprehend.

501
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:47,600
But you and I can heal the past.

502
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:51,600
Let me show you how
powerful our element can be.

503
00:36:51,850 --> 00:36:53,600
When airbenders work together.

504
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,767
What are you doing?

505
00:36:59,601 --> 00:37:01,600
This is how Sonam taught me.

506
00:37:01,601 --> 00:37:04,600
Feel the energy that tethers us.

507
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:11,600
The bond between us.

508
00:37:11,601 --> 00:37:13,600
Can you feel it?

509
00:37:13,601 --> 00:37:14,600
Use it!

510
00:37:14,601 --> 00:37:15,600
This is amazing!

511
00:37:15,601 --> 00:37:17,600
Yes!

512
00:37:17,601 --> 00:37:19,101
Woohoo!

513
00:37:22,601 --> 00:37:24,600
Oh yeah!

514
00:37:24,601 --> 00:37:25,600
Human boomerang!

515
00:37:25,601 --> 00:37:26,600
He's actually flying.

516
00:37:26,601 --> 00:37:28,600
So are we.

517
00:37:28,601 --> 00:37:29,600
Whoa!

518
00:37:29,601 --> 00:37:30,600
That's my best friend!

519
00:37:30,601 --> 00:37:31,600
That's my best friend!

520
00:37:31,601 --> 00:37:32,600
Now you throw me!

521
00:37:32,601 --> 00:37:33,601
Now you throw me!

522
00:37:55,580 --> 00:37:58,813
I had no idea that you were going to die.

523
00:38:03,581 --> 00:38:05,980
This is only the beginning.

524
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:08,807
I can't believe it.

525
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:17,980
Airbenders will fill the sky again.

526
00:38:18,630 --> 00:38:20,420
We have been given a great gift.

527
00:38:21,420 --> 00:38:22,740
The chance to redeem ourselves.

528
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:26,040
You were destined to find
me on that mountain, Aang.

529
00:38:28,690 --> 00:38:29,700
How did you end up there?

530
00:38:34,410 --> 00:38:35,890
The Earthbenders had attacked Tirana.

531
00:38:37,210 --> 00:38:39,620
Sonim and I fought
fearlessly, side by side.

532
00:38:40,570 --> 00:38:41,930
We drove them back to Mount Baihu.

533
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:44,120
And that's the last I remember.

534
00:38:46,740 --> 00:38:47,980
She must have saved your life.

535
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:51,060
Only an Avatar could
have put you in that sphere.

536
00:38:55,060 --> 00:38:57,580
Aang, can I ask you something?

537
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,080
Of course.

538
00:38:59,820 --> 00:39:02,977
If the Fire Nation destroyed
the Air Nomads, how

539
00:39:02,989 --> 00:39:05,960
can you suffer the
presence of the Fire Lord?

540
00:39:09,260 --> 00:39:10,840
Zuko is a friend and an ally.

541
00:39:11,840 --> 00:39:14,320
He turned against his own
father to help me end the war.

542
00:39:15,310 --> 00:39:17,480
Yet he wears the crown himself now.

543
00:39:18,630 --> 00:39:21,160
Fire by its nature burns, Aang.

544
00:39:22,310 --> 00:39:25,420
Our kind have always suffered at
the hands of the other elements.

545
00:39:27,270 --> 00:39:28,680
That's why we built Republic City.

546
00:39:29,780 --> 00:39:33,280
To show the world that if we listen
to each other, we can all live together.

547
00:39:33,281 --> 00:39:34,420
In peace.

548
00:39:36,250 --> 00:39:39,840
And once we bring back
Airbenders, it'll be complete.

549
00:39:43,790 --> 00:39:47,800
When everyone stuck to their own,
the whole world was nearly torn apart.

550
00:39:49,100 --> 00:39:54,700
And besides, Katara, Sokka,
Zuko, Toph, they're my family now.

551
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:58,680
I want to live in a world
where we can all be together.

552
00:40:00,910 --> 00:40:02,820
You remind me so much of Sonom.

553
00:40:06,870 --> 00:40:08,680
It's the Avatar.

554
00:40:08,681 --> 00:40:11,440
And this time he's got
his friends with him.

555
00:40:11,890 --> 00:40:13,160
That's the Fire Lord's airship.

556
00:40:13,610 --> 00:40:14,560
How'd they get ahead of us?

557
00:40:14,561 --> 00:40:16,040
They don't even have the map.

558
00:40:16,290 --> 00:40:18,500
We can't risk him
getting to the staff first.

559
00:40:18,501 --> 00:40:19,380
Kill him.

560
00:40:19,381 --> 00:40:20,700
But he spared our lives.

561
00:40:20,701 --> 00:40:24,940
And how many Countless were killed in
the hundred years waiting for his return?

562
00:40:25,100 --> 00:40:27,720
Where was he when
your family was wiped out?

563
00:40:27,721 --> 00:40:31,420
If we want anything to change,
we need what the Benders have.

564
00:40:31,421 --> 00:40:32,421
Power.

565
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:34,740
Fire!

566
00:40:41,241 --> 00:40:42,808
It's the Denied!

567
00:40:49,081 --> 00:40:51,914
Oh, we are definitely under attack!

568
00:40:55,100 --> 00:40:57,040
Turn them up to his friends!

569
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,860
Is he crushing the ship?

570
00:41:11,761 --> 00:41:14,360
Targa?

571
00:41:14,361 --> 00:41:16,660
Targa, stop!

572
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:36,420
We're here.

573
00:41:42,921 --> 00:41:43,120
We're here.

574
00:41:43,121 --> 00:41:44,888
The Immortal Storm.

575
00:41:46,961 --> 00:41:48,660
Oh, no.

576
00:41:48,661 --> 00:41:51,494
There has to be another way around.

577
00:41:56,601 --> 00:41:57,120
No.

578
00:41:57,121 --> 00:41:59,500
Together, you and I can
clear a path for the ship.

579
00:41:59,501 --> 00:42:00,880
But we have to go now.

580
00:42:00,881 --> 00:42:03,860
Aang, trust me.

581
00:42:03,861 --> 00:42:06,894
Maybe now is a good time to turn back.

582
00:42:09,541 --> 00:42:11,480
I don't think that's an option anymore.

583
00:42:11,481 --> 00:42:13,180
Where are they going?

584
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:16,553
The engine's out.

585
00:42:22,921 --> 00:42:24,240
We're losing air pressure.

586
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:31,740
Targa, come with me.

587
00:42:31,741 --> 00:42:32,420
What about me?

588
00:42:32,421 --> 00:42:33,180
Take the wheel.

589
00:42:33,181 --> 00:42:33,820
What?

590
00:42:33,821 --> 00:42:36,540
I've only ever crashed
Fire Nation airships.

591
00:42:36,541 --> 00:42:39,020
Okay, let's see.

592
00:42:39,021 --> 00:42:39,660
Here's our rudder.

593
00:42:39,661 --> 00:42:40,440
This is the elevator.

594
00:42:40,441 --> 00:42:41,260
There's our ballast.

595
00:42:41,261 --> 00:42:43,760
And there's the giant tornado
that's going to kill us all.

596
00:42:47,300 --> 00:42:48,420
Follow my lead.

597
00:42:52,860 --> 00:42:54,360
Work with me.

598
00:43:00,861 --> 00:43:02,380
Just like I showed you.

599
00:43:02,381 --> 00:43:04,080
We can heart it.

600
00:43:14,460 --> 00:43:16,120
Yes, that's it, Aang.

601
00:43:16,121 --> 00:43:17,121
Keep going.

602
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:23,900
Got it.

603
00:43:30,401 --> 00:43:31,901
Zuko!

604
00:43:34,741 --> 00:43:35,780
Zuko!

605
00:43:35,781 --> 00:43:37,960
Aang and Targa are destroying tornadoes.

606
00:43:37,961 --> 00:43:39,020
But there's too many!

607
00:43:39,021 --> 00:43:40,300
But they're everywhere!

608
00:43:40,301 --> 00:43:41,760
Just steer the ship.

609
00:43:41,761 --> 00:43:42,760
Don't lose Aang.

610
00:43:42,761 --> 00:43:44,060
It's not that easy.

611
00:43:44,061 --> 00:43:46,080
Especially when everything is sideways.

612
00:43:46,081 --> 00:43:48,120
Okay, left!

613
00:43:50,140 --> 00:43:51,640
I did it!

614
00:43:58,141 --> 00:43:59,860
Right!

615
00:44:01,260 --> 00:44:02,760
Oh no!

616
00:44:09,261 --> 00:44:10,360
We're falling behind!

617
00:44:10,361 --> 00:44:13,040
I'm losing sight of them!

618
00:44:13,420 --> 00:44:14,380
We have to go back!

619
00:44:14,381 --> 00:44:15,860
Trust in your friends.

620
00:44:15,861 --> 00:44:18,100
They won't make it if
we don't clear a path.

621
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:25,780
Zuko!

622
00:44:32,281 --> 00:44:33,900
We're going to crash into the sea!

623
00:44:33,901 --> 00:44:36,520
When I give you the signal,
pull the lever next to the wheel.

624
00:44:36,980 --> 00:44:38,880
We're going to crash!

625
00:44:42,901 --> 00:44:44,260
Katara?

626
00:44:44,320 --> 00:44:49,320
We're going to crash into the sea!

627
00:47:14,320 --> 00:47:15,320
We made it through!

628
00:47:15,321 --> 00:47:16,321
Thank you, Taga!

629
00:47:17,120 --> 00:47:18,320
It was you, Aang!

630
00:47:18,321 --> 00:47:19,361
We're here because of you!

631
00:47:19,970 --> 00:47:21,410
Yeah, we're having a good time, too!

632
00:47:21,495 --> 00:47:24,320
You could have told us we were
flying into the Immortal Storm!

633
00:47:24,321 --> 00:47:26,320
I know it was dangerous,
but we had to risk it!

634
00:47:26,370 --> 00:47:27,370
We?

635
00:47:27,720 --> 00:47:30,320
I don't remember when
we took a vote on that!

636
00:47:30,321 --> 00:47:31,320
There wasn't time!

637
00:47:31,321 --> 00:47:32,320
I had to make a call!

638
00:47:32,321 --> 00:47:34,320
Friends, please, don't blame Aang!

639
00:47:34,321 --> 00:47:35,321
This is all my fault!

640
00:47:36,320 --> 00:47:37,560
I knew this would be difficult!

641
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:40,320
But Aang believed in
your strength as a team!

642
00:47:40,321 --> 00:47:43,320
And I'm honored to be a part of it!

643
00:47:48,570 --> 00:47:50,320
I forgive you, Taga!

644
00:47:50,470 --> 00:47:52,320
Everyone!

645
00:47:52,321 --> 00:47:53,320
Look!

646
00:47:53,321 --> 00:47:55,320
These islands!

647
00:47:56,420 --> 00:47:57,420
They were...

648
00:47:57,670 --> 00:47:59,320
Lion Turtles!

649
00:47:59,321 --> 00:48:01,320
Whoa!

650
00:48:01,321 --> 00:48:04,320
It's beautiful!

651
00:48:07,070 --> 00:48:08,320
Long before my time,

652
00:48:09,020 --> 00:48:12,320
the Lion Turtles granted the
gift of bending to humans.

653
00:48:13,120 --> 00:48:15,320
These are their final resting grounds.

654
00:48:16,220 --> 00:48:18,320
This is where Sonam
came to learn their ways.

655
00:48:18,445 --> 00:48:22,320
I am certain that she left her staff here.

656
00:48:22,770 --> 00:48:24,320
Where should we start looking?

657
00:48:24,321 --> 00:48:27,320
Aang, you must connect with her.

658
00:48:27,321 --> 00:48:31,320
But... No one can
connect with Sona.

659
00:48:31,321 --> 00:48:35,320
The spiritual power of the Lion
Turtles is still concentrated here.

660
00:48:36,070 --> 00:48:37,320
Let it guide you.

661
00:48:37,321 --> 00:48:38,361
We'll set out immediately.

662
00:48:38,495 --> 00:48:42,320
Actually, Taga, we could
really use your help here.

663
00:48:42,321 --> 00:48:45,320
If the Denied are close
behind, we need to be ready.

664
00:48:45,321 --> 00:48:48,320
Yeah, and we're gonna need more
than Toph's metal bending to fix the...

665
00:48:49,470 --> 00:48:51,320
My bending got us through that, Storm.

666
00:48:51,321 --> 00:48:52,320
What did you do?

667
00:48:52,321 --> 00:48:53,320
Steered with his feet.

668
00:48:53,321 --> 00:48:54,320
Repairs can wait.

669
00:48:54,321 --> 00:48:55,321
Aang needs me.

670
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:58,320
Taga, please.

671
00:48:59,220 --> 00:49:00,320
Stay and help my friends.

672
00:49:01,170 --> 00:49:02,320
I'll be okay on my own.

673
00:49:03,420 --> 00:49:04,420
As you wish.

674
00:49:05,220 --> 00:49:07,320
We will begin repairs for our voyage home.

675
00:49:09,620 --> 00:49:10,620
Everyone?

676
00:49:11,195 --> 00:49:13,320
I know I've asked a lot
of you on this journey.

677
00:49:14,070 --> 00:49:17,320
But we're about to accomplish
something that will change the world.

678
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:06,320
Let it guide you.

679
00:50:27,321 --> 00:50:28,320
Sona?

680
00:50:28,321 --> 00:50:29,321
No.

681
00:50:41,400 --> 00:50:45,433
Ah, this is turning out
to be a nice little vacation.

682
00:50:49,401 --> 00:50:54,060
Aside from all the people trying
to kill us, and the tornadoes...

683
00:50:54,061 --> 00:50:56,280
Um, we're supposed to be fixing the ship?

684
00:50:56,980 --> 00:50:58,020
You're doing great, buddy.

685
00:50:59,260 --> 00:51:00,120
Has anyone seen Taga?

686
00:51:00,121 --> 00:51:03,340
Yes, we've all seen Taga. He's so gorgeous.

687
00:51:03,640 --> 00:51:04,720
Jeez, I get it.

688
00:51:05,570 --> 00:51:08,180
Oh, I see what you mean.
He wandered off that way.

689
00:51:08,181 --> 00:51:10,720
No, maybe that way?

690
00:51:40,890 --> 00:51:43,523
Taga! Taga! Where are you going?

691
00:51:48,515 --> 00:51:49,720
Aang needs to be protected.

692
00:51:49,721 --> 00:51:51,220
I agree.

693
00:51:54,470 --> 00:51:57,854
I know my ways may
seem unusual to you, but

694
00:51:57,866 --> 00:52:01,420
I assure you, everything
I do, I do for Aang.

695
00:52:01,920 --> 00:52:04,120
For Aang? Or for the staff?

696
00:52:05,930 --> 00:52:10,560
You have no idea all that we've lost.
You've never known a world with airbenders.

697
00:52:11,460 --> 00:52:14,897
I know Aang. He may
be the last of his kind,

698
00:52:14,909 --> 00:52:18,280
but he's the reason
this world knows peace.

699
00:52:18,355 --> 00:52:22,655
His values as an air nomad
have brought balance to chaos.

700
00:52:32,210 --> 00:52:36,200
It's because of Aang that the water
tribes, Earth Kingdom and Fire Nation now

701
00:52:36,212 --> 00:52:40,060
work together, striving for harmony,
a peace we once thought unattainable.

702
00:52:40,220 --> 00:52:45,220
You speak of peace. There will never be
peace among the elements. There never was.

703
00:52:48,520 --> 00:52:51,740
Your precious Republic
City is built on lies.

704
00:52:51,741 --> 00:52:55,740
It's built on hope. Do you have hope, Taga?

705
00:52:56,000 --> 00:53:01,120
Saving my people requires more
than just hope. It requires sacrifice.

706
00:53:01,121 --> 00:53:05,220
I saw you try to crush the Danides
airships. You were ready to kill them.

707
00:53:08,000 --> 00:53:13,000
I know what kind of airbender Aang
is, but what kind of airbender are you?

708
00:53:42,020 --> 00:53:44,816
Aang did well getting us here.

709
00:53:44,828 --> 00:53:50,020
There is great strength in
him, but weakness as well.

710
00:53:50,195 --> 00:53:51,100
Weakness?

711
00:53:51,101 --> 00:53:53,220
Yes. You.

712
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:09,833
What the hog monkey?

713
00:54:38,000 --> 00:54:43,000
No!

714
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:39,000
Tata!

715
00:56:02,150 --> 00:56:03,650
Brother...

716
00:56:09,250 --> 00:56:11,000
Taga, it's real.

717
00:56:11,001 --> 00:56:13,968
We can finally bring back airbending.

718
00:56:19,100 --> 00:56:21,267
Let's go tell the others.

719
00:56:23,001 --> 00:56:26,000
We can do this. Me and you.

720
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:29,000
I can't do this without my friends.

721
00:56:29,400 --> 00:56:34,000
Earth killed my people. Fire killed yours.

722
00:56:34,001 --> 00:56:38,000
The staff is the only way we
can create a new air empire.

723
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:41,000
One capable of defending itself.

724
00:56:41,001 --> 00:56:42,001
No.

725
00:56:42,100 --> 00:56:44,000
We can build a new future, Taka.

726
00:56:44,225 --> 00:56:46,000
But it has to be for everyone.

727
00:56:46,150 --> 00:56:48,000
The staff doesn't belong to everyone.

728
00:56:48,325 --> 00:56:50,000
It belongs to us.

729
00:56:50,001 --> 00:56:51,000
What... what have you done?

730
00:56:51,001 --> 00:56:55,000
As long as they were around, you'd
always put them ahead of our people.

731
00:56:55,850 --> 00:56:57,000
Don't you see?

732
00:56:57,001 --> 00:56:59,000
This is how we redeem ourselves.

733
00:56:59,001 --> 00:57:01,000
It doesn't matter that you ran them.

734
00:57:01,001 --> 00:57:03,000
As long as you stand with me now.

735
00:57:03,001 --> 00:57:04,000
Now.

736
00:57:04,001 --> 00:57:05,000
Aang!

737
00:57:05,001 --> 00:57:06,000
Listen to me!

738
00:57:06,001 --> 00:57:07,000
Katara!

739
00:57:07,001 --> 00:57:08,001
This is the only way!

740
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:18,433
You're a traitor to your own.

741
00:57:24,001 --> 00:57:25,000
Just like Sona!

742
00:57:25,001 --> 00:57:26,001
Just like Sona!

743
00:57:54,000 --> 00:57:55,000
No!

744
00:57:55,001 --> 00:57:56,001
No!

745
00:57:57,000 --> 00:58:00,167
I wanted to do this with you by my side.

746
00:58:05,001 --> 00:58:09,168
But if I must build a new
air empire alone... So be it.

747
00:58:11,001 --> 00:58:12,001
So be it.

748
00:58:14,000 --> 00:58:15,700
There's no way in!

749
00:58:22,001 --> 00:58:23,000
We have to turn back!

750
00:58:23,001 --> 00:58:24,000
No!

751
00:58:24,001 --> 00:58:26,000
We keep trying to push through!

752
00:58:39,000 --> 00:58:41,000
So new staff!

753
00:58:41,001 --> 00:58:42,000
Denied!

754
00:58:42,001 --> 00:58:45,000
The Avatar is dead!

755
00:58:45,001 --> 00:58:50,000
If you wish to build a new world where
you have the power... I can give it to you!

756
00:59:05,300 --> 00:59:06,000
Appa!

757
00:59:06,001 --> 00:59:07,501
Katara!

758
00:59:13,250 --> 00:59:14,250
They're gone!

759
00:59:15,100 --> 00:59:16,100
It's all my fault!

760
00:59:17,275 --> 00:59:19,000
It's always been my fault!

761
00:59:19,650 --> 00:59:21,000
Ever since I ran away!

762
00:59:23,350 --> 00:59:29,000
No Avatar has ever fallen into such
shame as to join me here in my sorrow.

763
00:59:31,400 --> 00:59:33,000
Why do you grieve so, friend?

764
00:59:33,700 --> 00:59:35,000
Avatar Sonum?

765
00:59:35,001 --> 00:59:36,000
Taga murdered my friends.

766
00:59:36,001 --> 00:59:37,000
And now he has a staff.

767
00:59:37,001 --> 00:59:38,000
Taga!

768
00:59:38,001 --> 00:59:41,000
No!

769
00:59:41,000 --> 00:59:42,000
I... I stopped him!

770
00:59:42,001 --> 00:59:43,000
I hit the staff!

771
00:59:43,001 --> 00:59:44,000
What have you done?

772
00:59:44,001 --> 00:59:45,000
What have you done?

773
00:59:45,000 --> 00:59:45,000
You're the one who gave him airbending!

774
00:59:45,000 --> 00:59:45,000
How could you give power to a monster?!

775
00:59:45,000 --> 00:59:45,000
The Taga I gave bending
to was a different man.

776
00:59:45,000 --> 00:59:45,000
It was a different time.

777
00:59:45,001 --> 00:59:46,000
The airbenders were the
peacekeepers of the Four Elements.

778
00:59:46,001 --> 00:59:47,126
We used our power to mediate
all conflict with non-violence.

779
00:59:47,150 --> 00:59:49,000
But we were the fewest in numbers.

780
00:59:49,001 --> 00:59:50,076
We were the fewest in numbers.

781
00:59:50,100 --> 00:59:52,001
For many years, we existed in a
beautiful balance of great power.

782
00:59:52,025 --> 00:59:54,000
We used our power to mediate
all conflict with non-violence.

783
00:59:54,001 --> 00:59:55,000
But we were the fewest in numbers.

784
00:59:55,001 --> 00:59:56,126
For many years, we existed in a
beautiful balance of great prosperity.

785
00:59:56,150 --> 00:59:57,000
But the world began to shift.

786
00:59:57,001 --> 00:59:58,000
The earthbenders from the ground.

787
00:59:58,001 --> 01:00:01,000
Why did you give power to a monster?!

788
01:00:01,001 --> 01:00:02,000
The Taga I gave bending
to was a different man.

789
01:00:02,001 --> 01:00:07,001
Why did you give power to a monster?!

790
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:45,000
What did you give power to a monster?!

791
01:06:45,001 --> 01:06:50,001
Why did you give power to a monster?!

792
01:07:14,000 --> 01:07:16,000
Did you just come from
that temple in the sky?!

793
01:07:16,001 --> 01:07:18,000
I certainly did!

794
01:07:18,001 --> 01:07:20,000
It was my favorite hidey hole!

795
01:07:20,001 --> 01:07:23,000
Until that dark yucky energy
started corrupting this whole face!

796
01:07:23,200 --> 01:07:25,000
Please!

797
01:07:25,001 --> 01:07:27,000
We need your help getting up there!

798
01:07:27,001 --> 01:07:29,000
It's my duty to stop this!

799
01:07:29,225 --> 01:07:31,000
I'm the Avatar!

800
01:07:31,250 --> 01:07:33,000
Oooh!

801
01:07:33,001 --> 01:07:35,000
The Avatar!

802
01:07:35,125 --> 01:07:37,000
Let me have a squeeze at you!

803
01:07:37,001 --> 01:07:38,000
Okay!

804
01:07:38,001 --> 01:07:39,000
Now with this eye!

805
01:07:39,001 --> 01:07:40,000
And this eye!

806
01:07:40,001 --> 01:07:41,000
And this eye!

807
01:07:41,001 --> 01:07:42,000
Oh, don't forget this eye!

808
01:07:42,001 --> 01:07:43,000
Can we hurry enough?!

809
01:07:43,001 --> 01:07:44,000
Let me squeeze!

810
01:07:44,001 --> 01:07:45,000
Sniff check!

811
01:07:45,001 --> 01:07:48,101
Oh, that's Avatar material right there!

812
01:07:50,001 --> 01:07:51,000
Yes, it is!

813
01:07:51,001 --> 01:07:52,000
Oooh!

814
01:07:52,001 --> 01:07:53,000
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

815
01:07:53,001 --> 01:07:58,000
It appears the universe has brought us
together for a very important mission!

816
01:07:58,001 --> 01:08:00,000
Huh?

817
01:08:00,001 --> 01:08:01,000
To flee!

818
01:08:01,001 --> 01:08:03,000
To be alive!

819
01:08:03,001 --> 01:08:04,000
Wait!

820
01:08:04,001 --> 01:08:05,000
Come back!

821
01:08:05,001 --> 01:08:06,000
We're going to go away!

822
