Please!

824
01:08:08,001 --> 01:08:09,000
Great Spirit!

825
01:08:09,001 --> 01:08:10,000
Both of our worlds are in danger!

826
01:08:10,001 --> 01:08:11,000
No, no, no, no, no, no!

827
01:08:11,001 --> 01:08:13,000
I am not going back up there!

828
01:08:14,000 --> 01:08:18,567
Hmm, well when you put it like
that, it does make more sense!

829
01:08:22,025 --> 01:08:27,000
Upon reflection, I've decided I shall
help you and your humany friends!

830
01:08:27,001 --> 01:08:28,000
What did he say?

831
01:08:28,001 --> 01:08:29,000
Nice work, Momo!

832
01:08:29,001 --> 01:08:30,000
Alright!

833
01:08:30,001 --> 01:08:31,000
In you go!

834
01:08:31,001 --> 01:08:36,001
By the way, no eating anything you find
in my teeth, as I'm saving that for later!

835
01:08:38,001 --> 01:08:39,000
Ready!

836
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:39,000
Ready!

837
01:08:39,001 --> 01:08:40,000
Set!

838
01:08:40,001 --> 01:08:41,000
Get steady and rent!

839
01:08:41,001 --> 01:08:44,000
The one and the two and
the you know what to do!

840
01:08:44,001 --> 01:08:45,000
Bluff!

841
01:08:45,001 --> 01:08:49,768
I know we haven't known each
other very long, but... I love you!

842
01:08:54,001 --> 01:08:56,000
You don't have to say it back!

843
01:08:56,001 --> 01:08:57,000
Hey!

844
01:08:57,001 --> 01:08:58,000
You got your hair back!

845
01:08:58,001 --> 01:08:59,000
Why are my eyes teary?

846
01:08:59,001 --> 01:09:00,000
Was I crying?

847
01:09:00,001 --> 01:09:01,000
No way!

848
01:09:01,001 --> 01:09:02,000
Look!

849
01:09:02,001 --> 01:09:03,000
What?

850
01:09:03,001 --> 01:09:04,000
What is it?

851
01:09:04,001 --> 01:09:05,000
It's Republic City!

852
01:09:05,001 --> 01:09:06,000
We can't let him destroy
everything we built!

853
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:06,000
We won't!

854
01:09:06,001 --> 01:09:07,000
We can't let him destroy
everything we built!

855
01:09:07,001 --> 01:09:08,000
We won't!

856
01:09:08,001 --> 01:09:09,000
We can't let him destroy
everything we built!

857
01:09:09,001 --> 01:09:10,001
We won't!

858
01:09:10,100 --> 01:09:15,100
We can't let him destroy
everything we built!

859
01:09:23,001 --> 01:09:25,000
Boomerang!

860
01:09:53,000 --> 01:09:54,500
Boomerang!

861
01:09:57,001 --> 01:09:59,000
Give me the staff, Targa!

862
01:09:59,001 --> 01:10:01,000
I see I underestimated you, Avatar.

863
01:10:01,001 --> 01:10:04,000
Your friends are stronger than I thought.

864
01:10:04,001 --> 01:10:06,000
But you're too late.

865
01:10:07,000 --> 01:10:08,500
They're denied.

866
01:10:15,100 --> 01:10:18,000
You see, I did what you wanted, Aang.

867
01:10:18,001 --> 01:10:21,000
I returned airbending to the world.

868
01:10:23,000 --> 01:10:24,000
What's the plan?

869
01:10:24,001 --> 01:10:25,000
We'll deal with the denied.

870
01:10:25,001 --> 01:10:27,000
You have to get the staff.

871
01:10:27,600 --> 01:10:30,000
I will rebuild Jurana on
the ruins of our enemies.

872
01:10:30,001 --> 01:10:32,000
Just as they did on ours.

873
01:10:32,001 --> 01:10:35,000
A new air empire will rise.

874
01:10:35,001 --> 01:10:37,000
Kill them all.

875
01:10:53,000 --> 01:10:57,000
We have to get these people out of here.

876
01:10:57,001 --> 01:10:58,000
Get out of here!

877
01:10:58,001 --> 01:10:59,501
Help me!

878
01:11:08,001 --> 01:11:10,000
Oh, yeah!

879
01:11:10,001 --> 01:11:11,001
Targa!

880
01:11:11,050 --> 01:11:13,000
Give it to me!

881
01:11:13,001 --> 01:11:14,000
This isn't the way!

882
01:11:14,001 --> 01:11:15,000
We can use the staff to bring back balance!

883
01:11:15,001 --> 01:11:16,000
Peace!

884
01:11:16,001 --> 01:11:19,000
You care so much about your
ideals that you'd let your people die!

885
01:11:19,001 --> 01:11:22,000
I will do anything to
make sure they survive!

886
01:11:30,000 --> 01:11:33,500
I will do anything to
make sure they survive!

887
01:11:38,001 --> 01:11:43,001
I will do anything to kill you!

888
01:12:08,000 --> 01:12:13,000
I will kill you!

889
01:12:24,001 --> 01:12:25,001
Don't do this!

890
01:12:25,200 --> 01:12:26,000
You have the power now!

891
01:12:26,001 --> 01:12:28,000
You can decide how to use it!

892
01:12:28,001 --> 01:12:29,000
I'm not like you!

893
01:12:29,001 --> 01:12:31,000
The world hasn't been good to me!

894
01:12:31,001 --> 01:12:33,000
The world is what we make it!

895
01:12:33,001 --> 01:12:34,001
Get away from her!

896
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:39,000
Run!

897
01:12:39,001 --> 01:12:40,001
Run!

898
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:00,500
Taga!

899
01:13:07,001 --> 01:13:08,000
Stop!

900
01:13:08,001 --> 01:13:09,000
You betrayed me!

901
01:13:09,001 --> 01:13:10,000
You betrayed our culture!

902
01:13:10,001 --> 01:13:11,000
I gave you every chance to see the truth!

903
01:13:11,001 --> 01:13:13,000
Shouldn't you be in the Fire Nation?!

904
01:13:13,001 --> 01:13:15,000
I'm fighting for the peace of all nations!

905
01:13:15,001 --> 01:13:16,000
Big talk from someone who sits at
a throne built on a century of war!

906
01:13:16,001 --> 01:13:17,501
Oh!

907
01:13:22,001 --> 01:13:25,700
Shouldn't you be in the Fire Nation?

908
01:13:25,701 --> 01:13:30,000
I'm fighting for the peace of all nations.

909
01:13:30,001 --> 01:13:35,001
Big talk from someone who sits at
a throne built on a century of war!

910
01:13:57,000 --> 01:14:00,700
I'm still the greatest
Earthbender in the world!

911
01:14:22,000 --> 01:14:23,500
Oh no.

912
01:14:28,001 --> 01:14:30,000
I'm out of water!

913
01:14:30,001 --> 01:14:31,501
We gotcha!

914
01:14:34,001 --> 01:14:37,000
And there's no Avatar here to save you.

915
01:14:37,001 --> 01:14:38,501
Suck a cycle!

916
01:14:41,001 --> 01:14:46,001
Let's see if your fancy new bending can
beat some good old non-bending know-how.

917
01:14:52,000 --> 01:14:54,000
Oh no!

918
01:14:54,001 --> 01:14:55,501
Bombs away!

919
01:14:58,001 --> 01:14:59,834
You just got denied!

920
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:09,500
Let's go!

921
01:15:16,001 --> 01:15:17,081
Good luck saving your city!

922
01:15:22,000 --> 01:15:25,233
We have to save as many people as we can!

923
01:15:27,001 --> 01:15:29,000
We have to save as many people as we can!

924
01:15:29,001 --> 01:15:34,001
Oh no!

925
01:15:46,001 --> 01:15:48,000
I know your pain!

926
01:15:48,001 --> 01:15:49,000
I know what you've been through!

927
01:15:49,001 --> 01:15:51,000
You don't know!

928
01:15:51,050 --> 01:15:57,000
I watched as all of my brothers
and sisters were slaughtered!

929
01:15:57,001 --> 01:16:01,000
And the Fire Nation burned
the Air Nomads to ash!

930
01:16:01,001 --> 01:16:03,000
Where were you?

931
01:16:03,001 --> 01:16:05,000
You ran!

932
01:16:06,000 --> 01:16:07,000
Ah!

933
01:16:07,001 --> 01:16:08,001
Ah!

934
01:16:19,000 --> 01:16:20,500
Chaga!

935
01:16:37,000 --> 01:16:38,000
No!

936
01:16:57,000 --> 01:17:00,967
The full power of the spirit
world flows through me!

937
01:17:06,000 --> 01:17:08,000
This is what strength looks like!

938
01:17:10,000 --> 01:17:12,700
This is what strength looks like!

939
01:17:36,000 --> 01:17:41,000
No!

940
01:18:48,980 --> 01:18:53,980
Oh, my God.

941
01:20:14,120 --> 01:20:16,487
We could have been brothers.

942
01:20:22,121 --> 01:20:24,580
We could have done this together.

943
01:20:24,581 --> 01:20:27,280
It didn't have to end like this.

944
01:20:27,281 --> 01:20:28,781
It's Aang.

945
01:20:33,101 --> 01:20:34,120
He's got the staff.

946
01:20:34,121 --> 01:20:34,700
Yeah.

947
01:20:34,701 --> 01:20:36,740
Kick his butt, Mega Aang.

948
01:20:36,840 --> 01:20:38,300
No, something's wrong.

949
01:20:38,301 --> 01:20:40,260
The power is corrupting him.

950
01:20:58,550 --> 01:21:02,380
I dreamt of bringing the Air Nomads
back to the world as peacekeepers.

951
01:21:02,381 --> 01:21:07,280
They could have been a beacon of light
for the world to follow, but you ruined it.

952
01:21:07,281 --> 01:21:09,680
You twisted my dream into a nightmare.

953
01:21:10,600 --> 01:21:14,080
Finally, you have the
power the Air Nomads need.

954
01:21:14,081 --> 01:21:16,700
Maybe there is hope for you after all.

955
01:21:20,160 --> 01:21:21,660
Do it.

956
01:21:28,161 --> 01:21:29,960
Use the staff.

957
01:21:29,961 --> 01:21:32,920
Show me you have the
strength to bring our people back.

958
01:21:32,921 --> 01:21:35,100
Do it.

959
01:21:35,101 --> 01:21:37,668
No! No! No! No! No! No! No! No!

960
01:22:22,150 --> 01:22:26,162
Aang. You will do so many great things
as the avatar. But you must be prepared to

961
01:22:26,174 --> 01:22:30,100
do what frightens you the most. Your
people, your home, we are always with you.

962
01:22:35,100 --> 01:22:38,100
Aang. No!

963
01:22:39,100 --> 01:22:40,600
No!

964
01:23:07,100 --> 01:23:08,600
Aang!

965
01:23:15,101 --> 01:23:16,601
No! My power!

966
01:23:32,550 --> 01:23:34,983
Aang. No! No! No! No! No! No!

967
01:23:39,400 --> 01:23:44,400
You fool! Why? Why did you break it?
We could have fixed everything!

968
01:23:47,101 --> 01:23:51,534
We can't erase the pain of the past.
We couldn't save them.

969
01:23:53,101 --> 01:23:57,100
But it's our duty to protect our people!

970
01:23:57,101 --> 01:24:01,100
Not at the cost of betraying
everything they stood for.

971
01:24:01,101 --> 01:24:02,100
No!

972
01:24:02,101 --> 01:24:04,100
It's time to let go.

973
01:24:04,101 --> 01:24:07,100
You have to forgive yourself.

974
01:24:10,300 --> 01:24:12,100
I have to forgive myself too.

975
01:24:21,400 --> 01:24:24,100
Air nomads are formed from the mist.

976
01:24:24,250 --> 01:24:27,350
We walk the world for a moment in time.

977
01:24:33,750 --> 01:24:36,583
Then we return to the eternal wind.

978
01:24:51,100 --> 01:24:52,100
Aang!

979
01:24:52,101 --> 01:24:53,601
Aang!

980
01:24:56,101 --> 01:24:57,601
Hey, Katara.

981
01:25:01,101 --> 01:25:02,101
Hey, Aang.

982
01:25:02,150 --> 01:25:03,650
Seriously?

983
01:25:06,850 --> 01:25:08,100
You do realize you're falling, right?

984
01:25:08,101 --> 01:25:10,694
Hey, if you ever get
tired of relying on alcohol,

985
01:25:10,706 --> 01:25:13,100
I could hook you up
with one of these babies.

986
01:25:18,100 --> 01:25:20,100
I'll give you the best friend discount!

987
01:25:35,125 --> 01:25:36,100
I don't know if
airbending will ever return.

988
01:25:36,101 --> 01:25:42,100
But I know now that the true power of
the air nomads was never their bending.

989
01:25:43,100 --> 01:25:44,100
It was their values.

990
01:25:44,101 --> 01:25:47,100
And that's a power I can pass on to others.

991
01:25:47,250 --> 01:25:53,100
Avatar Aang, you are the true
embodiment of the air nomads.

992
01:25:53,200 --> 01:25:57,100
Thank you for giving up
the power that I could not.

993
01:25:57,101 --> 01:26:01,100
You give me hope for
the future of our culture.

994
01:26:02,100 --> 01:26:03,100
And that's all right.

995
01:26:09,100 --> 01:26:11,133
It's amazing, isn't it?

996
01:26:17,101 --> 01:26:21,100
The first new air temple in centuries.

997
01:26:21,101 --> 01:26:24,100
Republic City is finally complete.

998
01:26:28,100 --> 01:26:30,100
A city for all nations.

999
01:26:30,101 --> 01:26:32,100
Just like you promised.

1000
01:26:32,101 --> 01:26:35,100
I never could have done
this without you, Katara.

1001
01:26:35,101 --> 01:26:38,100
Hey everybody!

1002
01:26:38,101 --> 01:26:39,100
Sorry I kept you all waiting.

1003
01:26:39,101 --> 01:26:41,100
Are you ready for our big trip?

1004
01:26:41,101 --> 01:26:44,507
As my new acolytes,
you will be helping me

1005
01:26:44,519 --> 01:26:48,100
preserve our culture
for future generations.

1006
01:26:49,100 --> 01:26:53,100
So, who wants to search for artifacts
at an ancient abandoned temple?

1007
01:26:53,175 --> 01:26:54,100
Yay.

1008
01:26:54,101 --> 01:26:58,100
I'm only going to make sure you don't
try to release another beefy old airbender.

1009
01:26:58,101 --> 01:27:01,100
Yeah, I'm done with bad boys.

1010
01:27:14,100 --> 01:27:15,100
Mr. Sodom told me about this place.

1011
01:27:15,101 --> 01:27:19,100
So, it's very possible that no one's
been here in hundreds of years.

1012
01:27:19,200 --> 01:27:22,100
Oh!

1013
01:27:22,101 --> 01:27:23,100
Is this an Arbender relic?

1014
01:27:23,101 --> 01:27:25,100
I think that's just a rock.

1015
01:27:25,101 --> 01:27:27,100
But I love the enthusiasm.

1016
01:27:28,300 --> 01:27:30,100
Aww!

1017
01:27:30,101 --> 01:27:32,100
Ah!

1018
01:27:32,101 --> 01:27:34,100
Keep your eyes open.

1019
01:27:34,101 --> 01:27:36,100
They never know what
we might discover here.

1020
01:27:36,225 --> 01:27:39,100
Oh.

1021
01:27:44,100 --> 01:27:47,100
I thought they were extinct.

1022
01:27:48,100 --> 01:27:49,867
I can't believe it.

1023
01:27:56,101 --> 01:27:59,100
The original airbenders.

1024
01:28:00,100 --> 01:28:01,867
Oh, can I have one?

1025
01:28:09,100 --> 01:28:10,100
Ha, ha, ha, ha!

1026
01:28:10,101 --> 01:28:11,100
Apo!

1027
01:28:11,101 --> 01:28:12,101
Yip, yip!

1028
01:28:39,100 --> 01:28:44,100
Oh, can I have one?

1029
01:29:26,080 --> 01:29:31,080
Oh, my God.

1030
01:31:30,080 --> 01:31:35,080
Thank you.
